17/10/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- On Thursday (16 October), Serbia- Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic and his Macedonian counterpart, Boris Trajkovski, welcomed the opening of UN-sponsored talks between Belgrade and Pristina on Kosovo. The two leaders agreed that the unresolved status of Kosovo remains a key factor for stability in the region.
In other news, the remains of 40 ethnic Albanians killed during the 1999 conflict were returned to Kosovo on Thursday. The bodies were discovered in central Serbia after the ouster of Slobodan Milosevic. (Utrinski Vesnik - 17/10/06; MIA, Makfax, AFP - 16/10/03)
